# Table filters (`src/app/shared/table`)

User portal list pages (transport, freight, warehouse — All + My) and **admin hub tables** (users, vehicles, warehouses on `/admin/home`) use the shared filter framework inside `DataTableComponent`. **Do not** build ad-hoc filter UI on list pages.

## File layout

| Piece | Path |
|-------|------|
| Filter types | `shared/table/table.types.ts` — `FilterDef<T>`, `FilterOption`, `FilterGroupMeta`, `TableChromeVariant`, `TableViewMode` |
| Apply logic | `shared/table/apply-table-filters.ts` — `applyTableFilters()`, `isActiveFilterValueForDef()`, `countActiveFilters()` |
| Chip + summary utils | `shared/table/filter-chips.utils.ts` — `buildFilterChips()`, `buildFilterSummary()`, `truncateFilterSelection()` |
| User filter partials | `shared/table/user-list-filter-partials.ts` — `routeCityFilters()`, `entityStatusFilter()` reused across transport/freight/warehouse |
| Number-range helpers | `shared/table/number-range-filter.utils.ts` — `isNarrowedNumberRange()`, `sanitizeNumberRangeValue()`, `clampNumberRange()`, `valueFromTrackPercent()` |
| Persistence | `shared/table/table-filter-storage.ts` — filter values, `panelExpanded`, and **`viewMode`** (`loadViewMode` / `saveViewMode`) in localStorage |
| Flyout shell | `shared/table/data-table/` — controls card + data card (default), toolbar, chips, right overlay flyout (full-screen ≤768px) |
| Filter bar | `shared/table/table-filter-bar/` — flat per-filter accordion list; `layout: 'flyout'` single column |
| Multi-select | `shared/table/table-filter-multi-select/` — searchable long lists (cities) |
| Option tiles | `shared/table/table-filter-option-tiles/` — short enum toggle tiles (status, vehicle type, cargo type) |
| Filter field chrome | `shared/table/table-filter-field/` — per-filter accordion header, clear, expand/collapse |
| Date range | `shared/table/table-filter-date-range/` — wraps `DatePeriodPickerComponent` (`variant="filter"`) |
| Number range | `shared/table/table-filter-number-range/` — **custom** dual-thumb slider (not native `<input type="range">`), summary line |
| Chips | `shared/table/table-filter-chips/` — one removable chip per filter dimension; `[compact]` input for mobile truncation + layout |
| Per-page defs | `portal/{user|admin}/features/<domain>/data/*-table-filters.ts` — export `*_TABLE_FILTERS` + `*_FILTER_STORAGE_KEY` |

Reference defs: user — `portal/user/features/transport/data/transport-table-filters.ts`, `freight/data/freight-table-filters.ts`, `warehouse/data/warehouse-table-filters.ts`; admin — `portal/admin/features/users/data/user-table-filters.ts`, `vehicles/data/vehicle-table-filters.ts`, `warehouses/data/warehouse-table-filters.ts`.

## Wiring a filtered table

1. Create `*-table-filters.ts` with `FilterDef<Entity>[]` and unique `*_FILTER_STORAGE_KEY` per list (All vs Our need separate keys — Our uses `.our` suffix, e.g. `bhcom-ba.filters.user.freight.our`).
2. In feature `*.table.ts`: `filters: ENTITY_TABLE_FILTERS`, `filterStorageKey` from scope factory (`buildTransportTable`, etc.).
3. i18n: `portal.user.features.<entity>.table.filters.*` for per-filter labels / placeholders; **all `dateRange` filters** use `shared.table.filters.period` (**Period** / **Period**) — not entity-specific period names.

```typescript
// freight-table-filters.ts (abbreviated)
export const CARGO_TABLE_FILTERS: FilterDef<Cargo>[] = [
  {
    key: 'origin',
    type: 'multiSelect',
    titleKey: 'portal.user.features.freight.table.filters.origin',
    placeholderKey: 'portal.user.features.freight.table.filters.allOrigins',
    options: BIH_CITY_OPTIONS.map((c) => ({ value: c.value, label: c.label })),
    searchable: true,
  },
  {
    key: 'status',
    type: 'optionTiles',
    titleKey: 'portal.user.features.freight.table.filters.status',
    options: [...USER_ENTITY_STATUS_OPTIONS],
    showStatusBadges: true,
  },
  {
    key: 'weightKg',
    type: 'numberRange',
    titleKey: 'portal.user.features.freight.table.filters.weightKg',
    min: 0,
    max: 5000,
    step: 50,
    unitSuffixKey: 'shared.table.filters.units.kg',
  },
  {
    key: 'neededByDate',
    type: 'dateRange',
    titleKey: 'shared.table.filters.period',
    field: 'neededByDate',
    singleDate: true,
  },
  { key: 'search', type: 'search', …, searchFields: ['description'] },
];
```

## FilterDef variants

| `type` | Use for | Notes |
|--------|---------|-------|
| `search` | Free-text | `searchFields`, `debounceMs`; inline in toolbar (not in flyout) |
| `select` | Single enum | Native `<select>` |
| `multiSelect` | Long searchable lists (cities) | `searchable`, `placeholderKey` |
| `optionTiles` | Short fixed enums (≤8 options) | `showStatusBadges`, `showOptionIcons`; multi-toggle tiles |
| `dateRange` | Period / needed-by | `field` + optional `endField` for overlap matching; optional `singleDate: true` for one-day filters (freight `neededByDate`) |
| `numberRange` | Weight, size, m² | `min`/`max`/`step`, optional `unitSuffixKey` |

Virtual filter keys (not entity fields): `search`, `transportPeriod`, `availabilityPeriod` — `key` is `string`.

## UX conventions (do not regress)

### Filter flyout
- Toolbar: inline **search** on the **left**; **view toggle** (desktop only, icon-only `2rem` square) then **Filters** toggle on the **right** (Filters remains rightmost — stable position — **no** Clear button in toolbar; no layout shift when filters activate).
  - **View toggle:** destination icons — `LucideLayoutGrid` (switch to card), `LucideList` (switch to table). `aria-label`: `shared.table.view.switchToCard` / `switchToList`. Hidden on mobile (≤768px always uses card view).
  - **Filters toggle:** `LucideFunnel` icon + **Filters** label on desktop; icon-only on mobile with active dot.
- **Desktop toolbar:** icon + **Filters** label; when collapsed + active filters, muted `{{count}} active` beside the label.
- **Mobile toolbar (≤768px):** search + filter icon **same row** (`flex-wrap: nowrap`); toggle is **icon-only** (`2rem` square) — hide **Filters** label and `{{count}} active` text. **Active-state dot** on icon corner (`.data-table-filters__toggle-dot`); `aria-label` uses `shared.table.filters.toggleExpandActive` when filters active. Styles live in `_table-chrome-split-card.scss` (global — SCSS budget).
- **Chips band** (below toolbar when `hasActiveFilters()`):
  - **Desktop:** grid `grid-template-columns: 1fr auto` — chips wrap in column 1; **Clear filters** (`.data-table-filters__chips-clear`) pinned **top-right** row 1 col 2.
  - **Mobile:** grid single column — **Clear filters** row 1 `justify-self: end`; chips row 2 full width. Pass `[compact]="isMobileLayout()"` on `app-table-filter-chips`.
  - Text-link style (`--text-secondary` → underline on hover); **not** a bordered toolbar button. Global layout: `_table-chrome-split-card.scss`, `_table-chrome-band-ladder.scss`.
- Controls in fixed right overlay (`layout="flyout"` on filter bar, **~30rem** desktop width); **mobile = full-screen** panel.
- **Flat per-filter accordion list** — no RUTA/ATRIBUTI/DATUMI section headers; each filter is its own collapsible row.
- `panelExpanded` persisted via `filterPanelStorageKey(filterStorageKey)`; default closed.
- **Collapsed + active filters:** muted `{{count}} active` on **desktop** toggle label — **no** numeric text badge on mobile (dot only). **Split-card (default):** entity hosts — **3px left + 1px top** `--entity-accent-spine` on controls + data cards (no filter-active border upgrade); neutral `3px` left on `.data-table-controls-card--active` when no `entityTab`. **Do not** add a second grey `border-left` on inner `.data-table-filters--active` (suppressed in split-card layout).
- Auto-open flyout on first non-search filter; close multi-select popovers on flyout close (`closeFilterDropdownsToken`).
- Escape, backdrop, and close button dismiss flyout.
- Row dividers: `--border-filter-divider` between filters in flyout list.

### Per-filter accordion (`TableFilterFieldComponent`, flyout only)
- **Default expanded** when flyout opens (flyout remounts each open).
- **Collapsed row:** filter name + grey summary + actions on the right.
- **Expanded row:** filter name + actions; controls below; summary hidden.
- **Toggle:** label + summary area is one button; chevron is a separate bordered icon button (matches flyout close styling).
- **Single `ng-content`** for controls — always mounted; hide with CSS when collapsed (do not put `ng-content` inside `@if` branches).

#### Collapsed summary (`buildFilterSummary()`)
| Filter | Summary |
|--------|---------|
| Cities / plain multi-select | Up to **2** full labels + `+N` (separate span, never inside ellipsized text) |
| Status (`showStatusBadges`) | Up to **2** `StatusBadgeComponent` + `+N` |
| Vehicle type (`showOptionIcons`) | Up to **2** `VehicleTypeDisplayComponent` + `+N` |
| Inactive | `shared.table.filters.all` (**Sve** / **All**) — same label for every filter type |

`+N` sits **immediately after** visible selections (not near Clear). Overflow count uses `FILTER_SUMMARY_TEXT_MAX_VISIBLE` (2) when more than 2 selected; else up to `FILTER_SUMMARY_MAX_VISIBLE` (3).

#### Header actions (right side)
- **Clear** (when active): `shared.table.filters.clearShort` visible (**Poništi** / **Clear**); `clearSelection` as `aria-label`; text-link style (underline on hover).
- **Expand/collapse:** bordered 2rem chevron button; `expandFilter` / `collapseFilter` `aria-label`s.
- Clear shown in **both** collapsed and expanded states when filter is active.

### Option tiles (`optionTiles`)
- Use for status, vehicle type, cargo type — not cities (keep `multiSelect` with search).
- **Status:** `app-status-badge` as tile content when `showStatusBadges: true`.
- **Vehicle type:** `app-vehicle-type-display` when `showOptionIcons: true`.
- **Cargo type:** plain text labels only.
- Selected: `2px` neutral border + subtle fill; unselected: `1px` `--border-table-filter`.
- Value model: `string[] | undefined` — same chips and apply logic as `multiSelect`.

### Multi-select
- Closed trigger: comma-separated labels for plain lists; **status** → `StatusBadgeComponent` (≤3 + `+N`); **vehicle type** → `VehicleTypeDisplayComponent` (≤3 + `+N`).
- Open panel: search → **ODABRANO** section → selected options → divider → unselected (sorted).
- **Search autofocus:** when the panel opens (`togglePanel`) or the accordion row expands while the panel is open, focus + select the search input via `afterNextRender` — user can type immediately without clicking the field.
- Option rows: `StatusBadgeComponent` or `VehicleTypeDisplayComponent` when flagged — not duplicate Lucide icons.
- Checkboxes: native control; `accent-color: var(--bg-pagination-active)`.
- Close panel when accordion row collapses (`expandedChange` on filter field).

### Date range (`dateRange`)
- UI: `TableFilterDateRangeComponent` → `app-date-period-picker` with `variant="filter"`, `allowPartial="true"`.
- **Label:** `titleKey: 'shared.table.filters.period'` for all entities (transport `transportPeriod`, freight `neededByDate`, warehouse `availabilityPeriod`) — chips, flyout accordion, and panel all show **Period**.
- **Range** (transport period, warehouse availability): default `mode="range"`; value `{ from?, to? }` stored under filter `key`.
- **Single date** (freight needed-by): set `singleDate: true` on the `FilterDef` → picker `mode="single"`; only `from` is used.
- Apply logic unchanged in `apply-table-filters.ts` — `matchesDateRange()` overlap rules for entity `field` / `endField`.
- Do not use twin native `<input type="date">` in filter UI — reuse `DatePeriodPickerComponent`.

### Number range
- Full bounds = **inactive** (not stored, no chip); summary shows `shared.table.filters.anyRange` when inactive.
- Dimmed track at full bounds; narrowed range shows values + optional `unitSuffixKey` in summary/tooltips.
- **Custom dual-thumb slider** — do **not** use stacked native `<input type="range">` (browser padding misaligns fill vs thumbs and allows visual overlap).
- Track + fill use shared thumb-inset math: `--number-range-thumb-size: 1rem`; bg/fill inset by thumb radius; thumbs positioned with `--thumb-pos` (0–1).
- **Drag constraints:** min thumb cannot pass max; max cannot go below min — enforced on every `pointermove` + `clampNumberRange()`.
- **Track click:** left half sets min, right half sets max (same positioning math as drag).
- Thumbs: `role="slider"` buttons with dynamic `aria-valuemin` / `aria-valuemax` reflecting live constraints.
- Helpers: `clampNumberRange()`, `valueFromTrackPercent()` in `number-range-filter.utils.ts`.

### Chips
- **One chip per filter dimension** — multi-select values grouped.
- **Desktop:** full selection in chip (status badges, vehicle types, comma-separated plain labels).
- **Mobile (`compact` on `TableFilterChipsComponent`):** chips stack full width (pill style unchanged — `border-radius: 999px`); **each chip is a single row** (`flex-wrap: nowrap`); truncate via `buildFilterChips(…, { compact: true })`:
  - Plain text / vehicle type: **1** visible + `+N` (`FILTER_CHIP_COMPACT_TEXT_MAX_VISIBLE`)
  - Status badges: up to **2** + `+N` (`FILTER_CHIP_COMPACT_BADGE_MAX_VISIBLE`)
  - Long values: ellipsis on value area; `+N` and remove button do not shrink
- **Status:** multiple `StatusBadgeComponent` — no duplicate label text.
- **Vehicle type:** multiple `VehicleTypeDisplayComponent`.
- **Plain lists (desktop):** comma-separated `valueText`.
- Range chips append unit from `unitSuffixKey`.
- Build logic: `buildFilterChips()` + `truncateFilterSelection()` in `filter-chips.utils.ts`.
- **Clear all:** `.data-table-filters__chips-clear` in chips band only — `shared.table.filters.clearAll` (**Clear filters** / localized); calls `tableStore.clearFilters()`. Do **not** duplicate in toolbar. Empty table also keeps inline clear link (`shared.table.common.emptyFiltered`).

### Empty state
- When `hasActiveFilters()` and zero rows: `shared.table.common.emptyFiltered` + inline Clear filters link.

### Layout

**Default chrome — split card** (`tableChromeVariant` default `'splitCard'` on `DataTableComponent`):

```text
.data-table-page (gap shows --bg-app canvas)
  ├─ .data-table-controls-card  — search + Filters toggle + chips band (with Clear filters link)
  └─ .data-table-data-card      — table / mobile cards + pagination
```

- Filters + chips live in **controls card**; table body + pagination in **data card** — visually separates “configure” from “read data”.
- Template uses shared `#filtersBlock` / `#dataBlock` `ng-template`s — do not duplicate table markup per variant.
- Optional `tableChromeVariant`: `'splitCard'` (default) | `'bandLadder'` (legacy single-card bands) | `'bandLadderLabeled'` (reserved). Host modifier: `data-table--split-card` etc. Global layout SCSS: `src/styles/_table-chrome-split-card.scss`, `src/styles/_table-chrome-band-ladder.scss`.

**Band stack inside controls card** (toolbar / chips separation):

| Band | Background token | Notes |
|------|------------------|-------|
| Toolbar | `--bg-table-filter-toolbar` → `--bg-surface` | search left; Filters toggle right |
| Inputs/buttons | `--bg-table-control` → `--bg-control` | |
| Chips band | `.data-table-filters__chips-band` → `--bg-table-filter-chips` → `--bg-inset` | **Desktop:** chips (wrap) + Clear top-right (`1fr auto`). **Mobile:** Clear row 1 right; full-width compact chips row 2. Neutral inset only — no entity wash. |

**Data card header row:** `--bg-table-header` (inset), `--text-table-header-size` (caption), semibold, uppercase, sticky + `--shadow-table-header-sticky`, `--border-table-header-strong` bottom rule.

- Flyout filter bar: single column (`table-filter-bar--flyout`); `padding` on each `.table-filter-bar__field` row.
- Inline filter bar (if used): 3 cols desktop, 2 cols tablet (`below-lg`), 1 col mobile — static `TableFilterFieldComponent` (no accordion).
- Filter panel/flyout: `--bg-table-filter-panel` (= `--bg-surface`), `--border-filter-divider`, `--shadow-table-filter-panel`. Full token map: `theme-tokens.mdc`.

