## Admin portal

Admin hub tables (users, vehicles, warehouses) use the same framework as the user portal:

- Colocated `portal/admin/features/<entity>/data/*-table-filters.ts` + `filterStorageKey` (`bhcom-ba.filters.admin.*`) on `*.table.ts`
- Mock services apply filters via shared `applyTableFilters()` (not inline `search`/`select` loops)
- **Users:** permission `optionTiles` (`BOOLEAN_FILTER_OPTIONS`), `dateOfBirth` `dateRange` (`singleDate`), toolbar search
- **Vehicles:** `vehicleType` / `vrstaGoriva` `optionTiles` (icons on vehicle type), four registration `dateRange` filters, expanded search over string + numeric fields
- **Warehouses:** city `multiSelect`, type `optionTiles`, capacity/height/floors/racks `numberRange`, facility booleans `optionTiles`, toolbar search

i18n: `portal.admin.features.<entity>.table.filters.*`; reuse `shared.common.booleanYes` / `booleanNo` for boolean tiles; all `dateRange` filters use `shared.table.filters.period` except vehicle-specific date labels where distinct titles are needed.

## Do not

- Rebuild filter bar, chips, or panel outside `DataTableComponent`.
- Reintroduce grouped section headers / `groupSections` in flyout without explicit product ask.
- Put `ng-content` in mutually exclusive `@if` branches in `TableFilterFieldComponent` (breaks projection).
- Embed `+N` inside ellipsized summary text strings.
- Use inline Lucide icons for vehicle type in filters/chips — use `VehicleTypeDisplayComponent`.
- Treat full number-range bounds as an active filter.
- Use portal accent on filter controls (sliders, checkboxes, clear links stay neutral).
- Reintroduce native dual `<input type="range">` for number-range filters — use custom thumbs in `table-filter-number-range/`.
- Use twin native `<input type="date">` in filter date-range UI — use `DatePeriodPickerComponent`.
- Use `--entity-*` service colors on table card chrome when `DataTableComponent` has `entityTab` — **3px left + 1px top** on controls + data cards; filter state via chips/count/dot. See `entity-service-colors.mdc`. Never stack entity spine on `.data-table-controls-card` **and** a grey `border-left` on inner `.data-table-filters--active`.
- Re-add **text** count badge on Filters toggle (mobile uses dot + `aria-label` only).
- Put **Clear filters** (`clearAll`) back in the toolbar next to the Filters toggle — bulk clear belongs in the chips band only.
- Use flex-wrap on the **desktop** chips band row to position Clear — use grid `1fr auto` so Clear stays top-right when chips wrap.
- Let compact/mobile chips wrap to a second line inside one chip — use `nowrap` + truncation/`+N`.
- Use entity-specific date filter labels (`Transport period`, `Needed by`, `Availability period`) — use `shared.table.filters.period`.

